# Build outputs (all .NET projects)
**/bin/
**/obj/
tools/runtime/publish/

# Packaged EXE (binary artifact — rebuild with dotnet publish before packaging)
tools/admin/runtime/CircuitOS.exe

# Release packages (built by Build-CircuitOSPackage.ps1)
dist/

# Local secrets — Appwrite connection (NEVER commit the real one)
appwrite.local.json
.env
.env.local

# Local secrets — Twitch OAuth app credentials + cached tokens (NEVER commit)
twitch.local.json
twitch-tokens.local.json
twitch-bot-tokens.local.json

# Machine-specific runtime settings (data backend choice etc.) — lives in the data root, not the repo
circuitos-settings.json
data/circuitos-settings.json

# Local dev-preview config (machine-specific absolute paths)
.claude/launch.json

# Runtime-generated profile data (the repo keeps only the flat starter template in data/).
# Running the app against data/ migrates it into profiles/ + writes overlay statics — never commit those.
data/profiles/
data/active-profile

# OS / folder junk
desktop.ini
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# Internal working / collaboration docs — kept locally for development, not published to the repo.
# (Product docs, README, versioning, and patch notes stay tracked.)
AGENTS.md
HANDOFF.md
HANDOFF-archive.md
UI.md
UX.md
docs/design-language.md
docs/feature-requests-analysis.md
docs/updater-velopack-plan.md
docs/dotnet-runtime.md
docs/0.7-appwrite-dev-setup.md
docs/0.7-cloud-foundation.md
docs/0.7-twitch-auth-setup.md

# Mobile companion project — separate app, not part of the desktop repo
ios/
